        G'day ! (Claimed Australian slang)<br/>
        And Merry Christmas to you all. I hope you had a lovely one.

        My Christmas Eve was a bit uncanny this year, flying on Christmas Eve from Tasmania to Melbourne, and cooking kangaroo burgers at a public barbecue on the 25th while playing Frisbee under a 30Â° sunshine.

        It was a enriching trip though, socially and culturally speaking. It started with 9 days of volunteering for an huge and quite famous event in Victoria, the Great Victorian Bike Ride.

        Imagine you gathering some friends and having a small bike ride in the countryside. This was pretty much how this event felt like, albeit this one gathered 5200 riders and 400 volunteers, riding 500km over nine days and taking place in the iconic Great Ocean Road. A bit challenging but definitely not a race at all, this events aims at having some good and friendly time with people enjoying bicycles.

        Volunteers were split into 35 groups and most of them didn't have to ride, carried from campsite to campsite by several coaches. They provide much of the labour for the ride, which helps keep costs down and therefore lowers entry fees for riders. They are in charge with pitching tents, serving meals, medical service, handling luggage, entertaining and so on.

